3.text: a) It is a small, white flower. You can see this in your garden. Women wear this in their hair. It is important for weddings, religious and cultural activities. A garland of this flower is very popular among Hindus. Its name starts with 'J'. What is it? J _ _ _ _ _ _ b) It is a round fruit. Its colour is its name. It has segments inside. Its seeds are called pips. It is a source of vitamins B and C and fibre. It helps to have good health. We can make a delicious drink from it. It is sweet and sour. Its name starts with 'O'. What is it?
